The Telegraph - Calcutta : Business

 Business Briefs

 New Delhi, July 13: Chartered and cost accountants as well as company secretaries have been exempted from service tax for certain services related to the representation of clients before any statutory authority. All other services rendered by them would attract a 12 per cent service tax. The decision has been taken following representations by these professionals requesting the government to exempt these services as similar services provided by other professionals like lawyers are exempted from the levy. 

 New Delhi, July 13: The department of telecom has ruled out allowing 74 per cent foreign direct investment through the automatic route, as it is not feasible in the nation?s interest.

 New Delhi, July 13: To prevent the sale of real estate assets of PSUs at below market prices during closure or divestment, the government has directed them to update their fixed assets records and inform the administrative ministries if their legal status was not clear.

 New Delhi, July 13: The one-man T.R. Rustagi Committee reviewing the services tax is likely to submit its report to the finance ministry in August.

 Mumbai, July 13: LML has allotted about 27 lakh equity shares to Merrill Lynch Capital Markets upon conversion of foreign currency convertible bonds.




